      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/22/2/10/78",
      "text": [
        " النَّاقُورِ قال: إنّ منّا إماماً مستتراً، فإذا أراد الله عزَّ ذِكره إظهارَ أمرِه نكت في قلبه نكتةً فظهر فقامَ بأمر الله ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.abdullah-al-shahin": [
          "(40) Muhammad bin Ya’qoob narrated from Abu Ali al-Ash’ari from Muhammad bin Hassaan from Muhammad bin Ali from Abdullah bin al-Qassim from al-Mufadhdhal bin Umar that Abu Abdullah as-Sadiq (as) had been asked about this Qur’anic verse, “For when the trumpet is sounded,”and he had said: “From among us there will be a hidden imam. When Allah wants him to rise, He will prick him in the heart and he will appear to execute the order of Allah.”"
        ]
      }
    },
